      Methods in edu.sjsu.cmpe275.api.controller.implementation that return types with arguments of type Employee 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Employee> EmployeeAPIController.createEmployee(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String email, java.lang.String title, java.lang.String street, java.lang.String city, java.lang.String state, java.lang.String zip, java.lang.Long employerId, java.lang.Long managerId, java.lang.String format)
      This API creates a employee object.

      For simplicity, all the employee fields (name, email, street, city, employer, etc), except ID and collaborators, are passed in as query parameters.
      org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Employee> EmployeeAPIController.deleteEmployee(java.lang.Long id, java.lang.String format)
      This API deletes the employee object with the given ID.

      If the employee with the given ID does not exist, return 404.

      If the employee still has a report, deletion is not allowed, hence return 400.

      Otherwise, delete the employee within a transaction
      Remove any reference of this employee from your persistence of collaboration relations
      If successful, HTTP status code 200 and the deleted employee in the given format, with all values prior to the deletion.
      Please follow the JSON format given above; i.e., all the fields, if present, are required.
      org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Employee> EmployeeAPIController.getEmployee(java.lang.Long id, java.lang.String format)
      This returns a full employee object with the given ID in the given format in its HTTP payload.

      All existing fields, including the optional employer and list of collaborators should be returned.
      org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<Employee> EmployeeAPIController.updateEmployee(java.lang.Long id, java.lang.String name, java.lang.String email, java.lang.String title, java.lang.String street, java.lang.String city, java.lang.String state, java.lang.String zip, java.lang.Long employerId, java.lang.Long managerId, java.lang.String format)
      This API updates a employee object.

      boolean EmployeeManagementService.updateEmployee(Employee employee, java.lang.String name, java.lang.String email, java.lang.String title, java.lang.String street, java.lang.String city, java.lang.String state, java.lang.String zip, java.lang.Long employerId, java.lang.Long managerId)
      updates the given Employee object, returns true if update is successful.
      Transactional method Changing an employee’s employer through the employerId follows following steps.

      If this person currently has a manager foo, all his/her current reports will report to foo.
      If this person currently does not have a manager, all his/er reports will changed to not have a manager.
      This person’s new manager (changed through the managerId parameter) must belong to the new company as well, or does not have a new manager.

    • Uses of Employee in edu.sjsu.cmpe275.utils

      Methods in edu.sjsu.cmpe275.utils with parameters of type Employee 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static boolean EmployerUtils.assignEmployer(EmployerRepository employerRepository, java.lang.Long employerId, Employee employee)
      Assigns Employer with employerId to an Employee.

      If employerId is null, method returns with false because employerId is a mandatory field for an employee.
      If there doesn't exist an employer with employerId, method return false indicating failure.

      Note: this utility won't save employee into database, all changes are in-memory
      static boolean EmployeeUtils.assignManager(EmployeeRepository employeeRepository, java.lang.Long managerId, Employee employee)
      Assigns Manager with managerId to an employee.

      If managerId is null, method returns true.
      If Manager with managerId doesn't exist, method returns false indicating failure
      If Manager's employer is not same as employee, method returns false indicating failure
      otherwise, assigns the manager and returns true.

      Note: this utility won't save employee into database, all changes are in-memory
      static void EmployeeUtils.fetchLazyAttributeFromEmployee(Employee employee)
      Fetches all the lazy attributes of current employee
